<dl id="n05069a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05069a">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05069a"> 69(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> child scream (singer) / babble (give ok) / talk</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A child&apos;s linguistic development covers three periods&mdash; the screaming time, the crowing or babbling time, and the talking time &hellip; Nurses say&mdash;and there is something in it&mdash;that the child who screams loudest as a baby becomes the best singer later. <small> Otto Jespersen, <a name="OJLN" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#OJLN"><cite title="source">Language: its Nature, Development and Origin</cite></a> (Jan 1922) 103-104</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
